program BasicTokens;
{ COR24 BASIC v1 — Token definitions, keyword table, and detokenizer.
  Compiles standalone as a self-test; will be merged into the full
  interpreter program.

  Token encoding per docs/design.md:
    Keywords:   0x80-0x97 (24 keywords)
    Operators:  0xA0-0xA9 (10 operators)
    Delimiters: 0xB0-0xB3 (4 delimiters)
    Variables:  0xC0-0xD9 (A-Z)
    Literals:   0xE0 (int), 0xE1 (string)
    EOL:        0x00

  NOTE: p24p limits — MAX_SYMBOLS=64, MAX_STRINGS=16, MAX_PROCS=32.
  Keep named constants minimal; use inline literals where safe. }

