cd ~/github/sw-embed/sw-cor24-pascal && gh issue create \
  --title "p24p: Add forward declaration support" \
  --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Summary

Standard Pascal supports forward declarations via the `forward` directive, allowing mutually recursive procedures/functions. p24p does not support this.

## What's Needed

```pascal
function expr: integer; forward;

function parse_primary: integer;
begin
  if token = '(' then begin
    advance;
    parse_primary := expr;  { calls forward-declared function }
    expect(')')
  end
  { ... }
end;

function expr: integer;
begin
  expr := parse_primary  { defined above }
end;
```

The `forward` directive declares a procedure/function signature without a body. The actual implementation appears later in the same scope.

## Why This Is Needed

Recursive descent parsers (like the BASIC expression parser) have mutual recursion between `expr` and `parse_primary` — expressions contain parenthesized sub-expressions. Without forward declarations, the only workaround is a single procedure with a level parameter, which is less readable and harder to extend.

## Workaround

Currently using a single `p_expr(level: integer)` procedure with if/else branches for each precedence level. Works but is monolithic.

## Standard Pascal Reference

Forward declarations are part of the ISO 7185 Pascal standard (section 6.6.1).
EOF
)" 2>&1

